=== Noun ===
'''electron'''

#The smallest [[particle]] that the [[atom]] contains.  It possesses a negative charge and it orbits the [[nucleus]].  Its movement is the cause of electricity. It has a [[charge]] of 1.602 × 10<super>-19</super> [[coulomb]].  See [[w:Electron|Wikipedia on Electron]] for more information.

See also: [[proton]], [[neutron]]

